6/2/15: BUT I HAVEN'T BEEN BACK!
There are way too many cheaper alternatives in the area now that get my dollars!

CARNIVAL RIDE: festive and funky New Orleans, open-air atmosphere;
KIND OF SMUG: cliquish bartenders and staff;
FAIRLY PRICED: Huge, dressed vegetarian chipotle dog and drink: $10.


First, I was very skeptical of a hot dog served over the counter and not from a wiener shaped French Quarter cart. But Dat Dog's brightly colored, large and funky open-air seating is so alluring that it's like a carnival ride you can't wait to get on.  Once inside it is comforting with that casually familiar uptown vibe present in neighborhood institutions like "The Boot", "Cooter Brown's" and "Igor's". Of course, if I wasn't local, I think the staffing might seem somewhat clubby and smug.  The dog was very tasty.  I had the vegetarian chipotle, recommended to me by many, dressed in jalapenos, salsa and sour cream on a very fresh bun.  It was so good that it reminded me of those old McKenzie's mouth-wateringly soft hamburger buns.  A Freret Find!
